two-sided markets$-$e.g., bilateral trade, double auctions, and combinatorial
double auctions$-$it is possible to design near-optimal mechanisms with
provable, constant-factor approximation guarantees with just a single sample
from the priors! In fact, most of our results in addition to requiring less
information also improve upon the best known approximation guarantees for the
respective setting.
